Project Director - United Arab Emirates
Job Seekers
|
|
what:
where:
Abu Dhabi
I am working with a leading international EPC company - providing engineering, design and construction services for the upstream, midstream and downstream oil and gas. The company is looking to continue to develop their operations in the UAE and are looking for a talented Project Director to lead the project operations in UAE.
Responsibilities:
Managing and overseeing five projects, with project managers reporting directly to you Providing guidance and direction to the teams of each project respectively Ensuring the projects under your management are completed within the client agreed time constraints Ensuring the project budgets are adhered to and that the clients are satisfied with the project execution
Skills and experience required:
Experience in managing projects ideally involving construction, pipelines, refineries and tankage projects in the oil and gas industry Experience of managing projects worth at last $500M A strong background in managing teams of at least 30 personnel A proven track record of providing strong direction to project teams and enabling projects to be completed within a timely manner.
Note: Candidates who do not meet the above requirements will not be contacted. As the role is based in United Arab Emirates, candidates must be willing to relocate to this region as the role is a permanent role.
